We recommend the Local Chief Executive to direct the following:
1) Require the Inventory Committee to conduct physical inventory on Property, Plant & Equipment and properly established the custody/ status of unreturned/missing/not-yet-returned properties to ensure correctness and reliability of the PPE account balances;
2) Require the accountable officer/employee to immediately apply for Relief from Accountability for the lost properties;
3) Require the General Services Officer to institute measure to properly dispose all properties found to be obsolete and unserviceable during the conduct of physical count;
4) Require the General Services Officer to maintain complete properly/equipment cards as required under Sec. 43 of NGAS, Volume I & Sec C. 3, Chapter V of the Manual on Property Custodianship; and,
5) Require the Inventory Committee to retrieve the records of the properties found to have no tags and facilitate the placement/attachment of such Inventory Tags/Stickers on all the properties for easier cross-examination with the AREs and proper identification of the properties.

